        "p_science": {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Goat milk has been used in skincare since Cleopatra. The reason it works: it naturally contains lactic acid — the same alpha-hydroxy that aggressive foot peels use, but at <strong>roughly 1/10 the strength</strong>. Strong enough to loosen dead skin in 30 minutes. Gentle enough that dermatologists routinely green-light it during pregnancy. No five-day peeling phase, no painful flake.</p>"
          }
        },
